Condition : 12 - The development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the following details:
(i)	A-02-400;
(ii)	MMD-346095-S-DR-00-XX-0001;
(iii)	Network Rail Survey (Structure Reference 7/14A);
(iv)	Network Rail Survey (Structure Reference X7/40A).
The underpass and ramp shall be constructed in accordance with the approved details and completed prior to the first use of the stadium and maintained in accordance with the details thereafter. Should the phasing require that the permanent ramp and underpass be completed following the first use of the stadium, details of any temporary ramp arrangements for access to the underpass shall be submitted to the Council for approval. The underpass shall be open to pedestrians, including members of the public, at all times, unless otherwise agreed in the Stadium Management Plan.

Condition : 13 - The development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the following details:
(i)	A-02-400;
(ii)	UN12473-BR-004 Rev. D;
(iii)	UN12473-BR-005 Rev. D;
(iv)	MMD-346095-S-DR-00-XX-1000;
(v)	Brentford Stadium East Access Bridge, Form F002 (NR/L2/CIV/003/F002: Statement of Design Intent) (April 2015);
(vi)	Brentford Football Club Lionel Road Stadium, East Access Bridge, Addendum to Approval in Principle Superstructure, Abutments and Foundations (April 2015).
The bridge shall be constructed in accordance with the approved details and completed prior to the first use of the stadium and maintained in accordance with the details thereafter. The bridge shall be open to pedestrians, including members of the public, at all times, unless otherwise agreed in the Stadium Management Plan. Vehicular access shall be restricted to emergency vehicles, authorised stadium employees and visitors, authorised ancillary commercial employees authorised residents and visitors of the Central East residential buildings, and for appropriate servicing only.

Condition : 15 - The development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the following details:
(i)	Sustainability Statement; 
(ii)	Code for Sustainable Homes Pre-Assessment Duffy Site; 
(iii)	Code for Sustainable Pre-Assessment Report Central Southern Site; 
(iv)	Code for Sustainable Homes Pre-Assessment Report Central Eastern Site; 
(v)	Code for Sustainable Homes Pre-Assessment Report Capital Court Site; 
(vi)	BREEAM Pre-certification Framework Report; 
(vii)	Environmental Sustainability, Brentford Community Stadium-CSH Ecology Credit Report A-02-400 (Received: 31 July 2016); 
(viii)	Rainwater Harvesting Evaluation (Received 22 September 2016);
(ix)	Energy Strategy dated September 2017;
(x)	BREEAM Pre-Assessment Report (Community Facilities) dated September 2017; and
(xi)	Energy Statement dated June 2018
The scheme as approved for each phase shall be implemented prior to occupation of that phase unless otherwise approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and retained and maintained thereafter.
Within 3 months of first occupation of the residential elements a Code for Sustainable Homes Final (Post-Construction) Certificate, and BREEAM Post Construction Certificate for the relevant aspects of the stadium, issued by the BRE or equivalent licensing organisation, must be submitted for the stadium or each dwelling in that phase to the Local Planning Authority to demonstrate that Level 4 or BREEAM Very Good has been achieved. All the measures integrated shall be retained for as long as the development is in existence.

Condition : 21 - The development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the following details:
(i)	Brentford Community Stadium and Residential Development Outline Summary Programme (Amended) Received 1 November 2016;
(ii)	Brentford Community Stadium, car park podium, residential podiums, new rail bridge and Lionel Road improvements works: Construction Logistics Management Plan - Phases 1-4 s278 works and main outfall drainage works received 1 November 2016;
(iii)	Construction Logistics Plan Phasing Drawings 1-6 Rev. 5, received 1 November 2016;
(iv)	Email from Prime Place received 13 December 2016.
(v)	Construction Logistics Plan: Brentford Community Stadium Project - August 2018, received 3 August 2018. 
Update reports detailing any amendments to the above approved documents (as required) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of future phases of development.

Condition : 23 - Drainage for the site shall be consistent with the measures outlined in the 'Brentford Community Stadium - Flood Risk Assessment' Revision 3 (UN12473fin-rep-FRA), with the drainage system to be designed to ensure:
(i)	The peak discharge rate from site no greater than the greenfield runoff rate to existing drainage infrastructure;
(ii)	A surface water drainage network capable of containing (with no flooding) runoff from a 3.3% probability rainfall event, including an additional allowance for climate change; and attenuation capable of containing on-site the runoff from a 1% probability rainfall event, including an additional allowance for climate change.
(iii)	Provision of appropriate attenuation storage on site, with provision for rainwater harvesting and a Sustainable Urban Drainage System (SUDS).
The development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with:
(i)	Below Ground Drainage Philosophy Statement for Brentford Community Stadium, dated 05 October 2016, received 11 October 2016:
(ii)	Design Note (below ground drainage) Brentford Community Stadium;
(iii)	LBH (00703/A/P11) Drainage Philosophy Report Condition 23 Responses Rev.01, dated 23 November 2016, received 02 December 2016;
(iv)	Storm Sewer Design (CCS-CP-161122.MDX, CES- SW-161110.MDX, 3847-HW-171116-SW NETWO;
(v)	Drawing 3847-CSS-320 Rev. P6;
(vi)	Drawing 3847-CES-320 Rev. P5;
(vii)	Drawing 3847-CCS-320(B) Rev. P2, and 3847- CCS-320(A) Rev. P4;
All dated 9 December 2016, and received 16 December 2016.
No discharge of foul or surface water from the site shall be accepted into the public system until the approved drainage works have been completed.

Condition : 27 - The development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the following details:
(i)	Written Scheme of Investigation for an Archaeological Evaluation (Central Eastern Site) dated 18/05/2015;
(ii)	Written Scheme of Investigation for an Archaeological Evaluation (Stadium Site) dated 18/05/2015;
(iii)	Written Scheme of Investigation for an Archaeological Evaluation and Watching Brief (Capital Court Site) dated 18/05/2015;
(iv)	Written Scheme of Investigation for an Archaeological Evaluation and Watching Brief (Central Southern Site) dated 18/05/2015; and
(v)	Written Scheme of Investigation for an Archaeological Evaluation and Watching Brief (Duffy Site) dated 18/05/2015.
Each phase of the development shall not be occupied until the site investigation and post investigation assessment has been completed in accordance with the programme set out in the Written Scheme of Investigation and the provision for analysis, publication and dissemination of the results and archive deposition has been secured.

Condition : 40 - That the association football events using the football pitch hereby approved which are open to the general public shall be limited to the following, unless otherwise agreed in writing:
a) Brentford Football Club first team competitive league games in accordance with fixture lists as agreed by the relevant football authorities (e.g. Football League);
b) Brentford Football Club first team cup games in accordance with fixtures agreed by the relevant football authorities e.g. The Football Association;
c) Brentford Football Club preseason friendlies, reserve, youth and ladies team matches; The screening of Brentford Football Club's first team away Association Football matches;
d) Three international matches plus pre match training sessions per annum; and
e) Two charity matches per annum.	
f) Local community matches including local leagues and schools, Brentford FC Community Sports Trust related sporting activities and corporate matches.
